toward death, his approach to gender, his interpretation of circumcision, the impact of his tales on Yiddish literature, and his hermeneutic theory. The combination of classic and new studies in God's Voice from the Void offers a window into the trajectory of scholarship on Hasidism, including ways in which contemporary scholars of Hasidism and Hasidic literature both continue and develop the work of their predecessors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh1 aDeutsch, Nathaniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorodetzsky, Samuel Abba, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKavka, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagid, Shaul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagid, Shaul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoskies, David G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTravis, Yakov, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiss, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolfson, Elliot R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZeitlin, Hillel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791489567423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791489567/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles